1
00:00:02,410 --> 00:00:05,140
(Episode 32)

2
00:00:11,150 --> 00:00:14,690
You seem very busy these days.

3
00:00:15,220 --> 00:00:17,590
Yes, things at the company
have been hectic.

4
00:00:17,590 --> 00:00:19,190
Especially with the Dream Resort project.

5
00:00:19,490 --> 00:00:22,490
Mom, did you see
Chef Kang Jun Ho's tattoo?

6
00:00:22,860 --> 00:00:25,730
Even his tattoo is so cool.

7
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:28,470
I saw he had some strange date tattooed
on the back of his neck.

8
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:33,440
I wondered if it had some special meaning,
but apparently it's his own birthday.

9
00:00:34,410 --> 00:00:36,470
I guess Chef Kang is pretty narcissistic,

10
00:00:36,980 --> 00:00:38,310
seeing he tattooed his own birthday
on himself.

11
00:00:39,480 --> 00:00:41,580
I heard he got it to cover up some moles.

12
00:00:42,010 --> 00:00:45,350
He has three moles in a row on his neck
that he thought were ugly.

13
00:00:51,960 --> 00:00:54,230
CEO Chae, is that really so surprising?

14
00:00:55,230 --> 00:00:56,230
What?

15
00:00:56,760 --> 00:00:58,500
I was just lost in thought.

16
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:02,700
He has three moles in a row
on the back of his neck.

17
00:01:03,230 --> 00:01:05,000
I also gave you his date of birth.

18
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:06,700
His name is Ha Neul.

19
00:01:07,840 --> 00:01:12,140
He has three moles on his neck.
That's so unique.

20
00:01:12,580 --> 00:01:16,050
Chef Kang Jun Ho makes anything look cool.

21
00:01:16,980 --> 00:01:18,320
You think that looks cool?

22
00:01:19,350 --> 00:01:22,920
But wait, does Chef Kang
tell you things like that?

23
00:01:23,420 --> 00:01:24,560
That it was to cover up his moles?

24
00:01:25,860 --> 00:01:27,060
It's not that he told me.

25
00:01:27,660 --> 00:01:30,560
He got it while studying in the US,
so that's how I know.

26
00:01:43,170 --> 00:01:45,580
No, it can't be.

27
00:01:46,210 --> 00:01:48,750
How could Kang Jun Ho possibly be my son?

28
00:01:49,780 --> 00:01:50,980
It can't be true.

29
00:01:53,020 --> 00:01:54,220
That must not be true.

30
00:01:55,120 --> 00:01:57,720
After how terribly I treated him...

31
00:01:59,460 --> 00:02:00,690
Let go of me.

32
00:02:12,770 --> 00:02:16,210
- What is it, Seo Rin?
- Mom, look at this! Quick!

33
00:02:17,580 --> 00:02:20,480
(1990.05.29)

34
00:02:20,850 --> 00:02:22,510
It's my Ha Neul's date of birth.

35
00:02:23,350 --> 00:02:25,380
May 29, 1990.

36
00:02:26,420 --> 00:02:27,490
It's so cool, right?

37
00:02:27,850 --> 00:02:32,120
It looks like Jun Ho's birthday is May 29.
I have to remember that!

38
00:02:34,460 --> 00:02:36,830
Mom, are you listening?

39
00:02:37,230 --> 00:02:38,360
What?

40
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:39,830
Yes, I heard you.

41
00:02:53,010 --> 00:02:54,150
What are you doing?

42
00:02:54,150 --> 00:02:55,210
That tattoo on your neck.

43
00:02:55,850 --> 00:02:58,350
- What do those numbers mean?
- Why the sudden interest?

44
00:02:58,420 --> 00:02:59,780
Just answer the question.

45
00:03:02,220 --> 00:03:04,020
She'll do anything to make me quit.

46
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:09,760
(Bomdama)

47
00:03:10,430 --> 00:03:11,600
Jang Mi, eat up.

48
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:13,500
You eat up too, Dad.

49
00:03:14,270 --> 00:03:15,500
I like Baek Ho.

50
00:03:15,500 --> 00:03:17,870
Jang Mi is so beautiful.
Baek Ho is so sweet.

51
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:22,240
You're right, Mom. The whole family
is having a feast in this nice place.

52
00:03:23,910 --> 00:03:26,380
Just look at how gorgeous this is.

53
00:03:31,180 --> 00:03:33,180
- Here you go, Mom. Be careful! It's hot!
- Eat up.

54
00:03:34,950 --> 00:03:36,350
So, Dad's treating us today?

55
00:03:36,490 --> 00:03:38,360
That's right. It's to help Jang Mi
get her strength back.

56
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:40,690
This is on me. Everyone, dig in.

57
00:03:42,490 --> 00:03:44,630
We get to eat our fill
thanks to you, Jang Mi.

58
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:48,670
This is delicious.
Suk Hee wants to eat this every day.

59
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:49,800
Bo Ra thinks it's delicious too.

60
00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:52,370
Bo Ra wants
to eat this every day, Grandma.

61
00:03:54,340 --> 00:03:57,640
It's so nice to have the whole family
together like this and share a meal.

62
00:03:57,780 --> 00:04:01,580
Next time the shop's closed,
what do you say we all go on a picnic?

63
00:04:01,650 --> 00:04:03,180
- That sounds great!
- I'd love that.

64
00:04:04,150 --> 00:04:06,480
Where should we go?
Bo Ra, where do you want to go?

65
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:11,760
What? Baek Ho told you to think carefully
about what you should give him?

66
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:13,320
Yes.

67
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:16,190
But I have no idea what he means.

68
00:04:16,360 --> 00:04:18,900
He just asked me to think
about what I could offer him.

69
00:04:19,560 --> 00:04:23,300
The way Baek Ho always looks out for you
is proof that he likes you.

70
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:27,510
Oh my gosh, he's asking for your heart!

71
00:04:27,510 --> 00:04:28,570
Your heart.

72
00:04:28,870 --> 00:04:30,910
What? My heart?

73
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:48,260
I have nothing to give you in return
except for some side dishes,

74
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:50,300
so why do you keep making me the taker?

75
00:04:50,300 --> 00:04:51,560
Who says you have nothing to give?

76
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:54,930
You have plenty to give me too.

77
00:04:56,130 --> 00:04:57,140
What are you talking about?

78
00:04:57,970 --> 00:05:00,440
Give me your heart, Jang Mi.

79
00:05:01,470 --> 00:05:03,470
I'll give you anything,

80
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:05,480
so please...

81
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:07,510
just like me back.

82
00:05:09,250 --> 00:05:10,780
Kang Baek Ho.

83
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:13,450
Kang Baek Ho.

84
00:05:15,890 --> 00:05:16,890
Director Ma?

85
00:05:17,420 --> 00:05:18,420
Jin Hong Ju.

86
00:05:18,990 --> 00:05:21,630
Don't you even think about
making a move on my Jun Ho.

87
00:05:22,090 --> 00:05:23,430
I'm warning you.

88
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:25,730
Don't worry.

89
00:05:26,260 --> 00:05:28,830
He and I are strictly
in a senior-junior relationship.

90
00:05:29,500 --> 00:05:32,270
Besides, there's someone I really like.

91
00:05:32,640 --> 00:05:34,840
What? Who is it?

92
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:37,180
It's too early to say.

93
00:05:37,610 --> 00:05:40,510
I'll introduce you
once things get more serious.

94
00:05:41,480 --> 00:05:42,650
He's totally my type.

95
00:05:44,050 --> 00:05:45,250
How lame.

96
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:46,920
Shit.

97
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:51,890
I'm home.

98
00:05:51,890 --> 00:05:54,990
My son's home. I'll call you back.

99
00:05:55,490 --> 00:05:57,430
Baek Ho, come sit here.

100
00:05:58,360 --> 00:05:59,360
Why?

101
00:06:00,060 --> 00:06:01,400
Why don't you go on a blind date?

102
00:06:01,500 --> 00:06:02,630
Not this again.

103
00:06:02,700 --> 00:06:05,940
No excuses. Just meet the girl
I set you up with.

104
00:06:06,900 --> 00:06:09,840
She'll be a thousand times better than
that girl who's nothing but bad news.

105
00:06:09,910 --> 00:06:12,740
- Mom, come on.
- What? I'm not deaf.

106
00:06:12,810 --> 00:06:15,950
Mom, you've never even met her.
Why do you always say she's bad news?

107
00:06:16,010 --> 00:06:18,650
Stop debating.
I've already made the arrangements,

108
00:06:18,650 --> 00:06:19,780
so you're going, and that's final.

109
00:06:23,620 --> 00:06:25,220
- Okay, I will.
- What?

110
00:06:25,220 --> 00:06:27,060
I said I'll go on the date.

111
00:06:27,460 --> 00:06:29,660
- I might as well go on the blind date.
- Seriously?

112
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:33,430
It's suspicious that you suddenly
changed your mind like this.

113
00:06:33,430 --> 00:06:35,030
What's so suspicious about it?

114
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:37,100
I said I'll go on the date.

115
00:06:49,080 --> 00:06:50,150
Think about it carefully.

116
00:06:51,220 --> 00:06:53,020
Think about what you can offer me.

117
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:54,890
I mean it, think hard.

118
00:07:00,930 --> 00:07:01,930
Mom.

119
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:05,300
I'm supposed to stay by your side forever,

120
00:07:06,400 --> 00:07:08,300
so it would be wrong to fall
for Baek Ho, wouldn't it?

121
00:07:09,870 --> 00:07:10,870
Mom.

122
00:07:11,770 --> 00:07:13,940
All I ever do is take from him.

123
00:07:14,570 --> 00:07:15,710
What do I do?

124
00:07:32,690 --> 00:07:35,690
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

125
00:07:41,430 --> 00:07:44,200
The photo and the moles on his neck...

126
00:07:45,700 --> 00:07:47,740
It really seems like Kang Jun Ho
is my Ha Neul...

127
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:54,750
- Tell Chef Kang to come to my office.
- Yes, ma'am.

128
00:07:58,150 --> 00:08:00,450
But once he's here,
what do I even ask him?

129
00:08:01,620 --> 00:08:03,290
No, maybe this was a mistake.

130
00:08:09,460 --> 00:08:10,460
Oh my...

131
00:08:16,970 --> 00:08:17,970
Hwa Young.

132
00:08:20,740 --> 00:08:22,740
What are you doing?

133
00:08:24,610 --> 00:08:25,640
Just for ten minutes.

134
00:08:26,210 --> 00:08:27,910
Let's just stay like this for ten minutes.

135
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:32,020
Please don't, Professor.
This is my office.

136
00:08:32,150 --> 00:08:33,450
Ever since I met you,

137
00:08:34,490 --> 00:08:36,750
my whole world
has been turned upside down.

138
00:08:37,190 --> 00:08:39,660
Whether I'm giving a lecture
or just sitting at home,

139
00:08:40,460 --> 00:08:43,260
all I can think about is you.

140
00:08:44,830 --> 00:08:48,030
I just can't help myself, Hwa Young.

141
00:08:58,910 --> 00:09:01,150
Let's go on a trip.

142
00:09:01,880 --> 00:09:02,950
On our trip,

143
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:05,720
we can watch the sunrise
and the sunset together.

144
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:08,220
I want to spend the whole day...

145
00:09:09,150 --> 00:09:10,760
nowhere else but by your side.

146
00:09:12,360 --> 00:09:15,360
I want to have you all to myself.

147
00:09:17,500 --> 00:09:19,200
Please, Hwa Young?

148
00:09:21,230 --> 00:09:23,370
All right. Some other time.

149
00:09:23,370 --> 00:09:24,470
Today...

150
00:09:28,210 --> 00:09:29,540
I'm expecting someone.

151
00:09:35,950 --> 00:09:36,950
Come in.

152
00:09:56,970 --> 00:09:59,800
Do you two know each other?

153
00:10:00,770 --> 00:10:02,010
What's with the looks on your faces?

154
00:10:08,080 --> 00:10:11,250
What's going on?
Do they know each other or not?

155
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:16,290
Come to think of it,
Professor Kang had the photo of Ha Neul.

156
00:10:18,490 --> 00:10:21,590
And why do Kang Jun Ho and my Ha Neul
have the same birthday...

157
00:10:21,590 --> 00:10:23,830
and the three moles
on the back of his neck?

158
00:10:24,830 --> 00:10:26,460
I can't just ask him outright.

159
00:10:27,200 --> 00:10:29,330
You called me in because
you had something to say, right?

160
00:10:30,970 --> 00:10:33,440
I had a question for you,
Chef Kang Jun Ho,

161
00:10:33,870 --> 00:10:36,540
but my guest just arrived.
Let's talk later.

162
00:10:40,710 --> 00:10:44,880
The professor is here on business
for Dream Resort.

163
00:10:45,580 --> 00:10:48,690
Anyway, we'll talk later. You may go.

164
00:11:05,700 --> 00:11:08,310
- Hong Ju.
- Mom, I'm running late for work.

165
00:11:08,610 --> 00:11:11,080
When you get to work today,
keep a close eye on Chae Hwa Young.

166
00:11:11,310 --> 00:11:12,310
How?

167
00:11:12,310 --> 00:11:15,710
If it looks like she's going somewhere,
call me right away.

168
00:11:15,980 --> 00:11:16,980
No, on second thought.

169
00:11:17,280 --> 00:11:21,320
I should just wait in front
of your hotel myself.

170
00:11:21,750 --> 00:11:22,920
That way, I can tail her.

171
00:11:23,190 --> 00:11:25,360
- Tail her?
- Yes, you silly girl.

172
00:11:25,790 --> 00:11:29,160
That's how I'll find out
if Hwa Young is meeting a man,

173
00:11:29,330 --> 00:11:30,800
and I can get to the bottom of this.

174
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:34,730
Okay, Mom. If she goes somewhere,
I'll call you right away.

175
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:35,800
Okay. Good.

176
00:11:38,970 --> 00:11:40,070
Okay.

177
00:11:57,860 --> 00:12:00,120
It doesn't look like
she's going anywhere, though.

178
00:12:02,630 --> 00:12:03,630
Do what for you?

179
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,330
You want me to pretend to be someone?

180
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:08,000
Yes. Please, just help me out
this one time.

181
00:12:08,370 --> 00:12:10,970
Come on, I've saved your life
a bunch of times.

182
00:12:11,470 --> 00:12:14,640
So now it's your turn to help me.
All right?

183
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:16,710
So you're saying I have to repay my debt?

184
00:12:17,340 --> 00:12:19,710
So this is what you meant
when you said I had something to offer?

185
00:12:21,880 --> 00:12:24,650
If you need my help, I guess I have to.
What can I do?

186
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:30,220
Jang Mi, I heard Lawyer Kang's mom
is nagging him nonstop to get married.

187
00:12:32,720 --> 00:12:34,260
Then you should just get married.

188
00:12:34,560 --> 00:12:36,960
How can you say that, Jang Mi?

189
00:12:37,460 --> 00:12:38,860
Can you really not see how I feel?

190
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:40,500
No, I can't.

191
00:12:41,030 --> 00:12:43,700
If your family tells you to get married,
then just do it.

192
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:47,670
I really don't get why you're suddenly
asking me to play a part for you.

193
00:12:47,870 --> 00:12:49,040
You're jealous right now, aren't you?

194
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:52,510
The thought of me marrying another woman
is bothering you, isn't it?

195
00:12:52,710 --> 00:12:55,950
No, I'm not. Why would you think that?
You're delusional.

196
00:12:56,010 --> 00:12:57,950
Come on, you're going to help me anyway.

197
00:12:58,620 --> 00:13:01,650
- You're just playing hard to get.
- What did you say? Playing hard to get?

198
00:13:02,120 --> 00:13:04,620
Hey, it was a joke. I take it back.

199
00:13:05,490 --> 00:13:07,790
Fine. Where do I need to go?

200
00:13:10,860 --> 00:13:12,030
Come on in, Jang Mi.

201
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,100
Why are we here?

202
00:13:16,130 --> 00:13:19,270
This is her. She has
a very important event to attend today,

203
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,800
so please take extra special care of her.

204
00:13:21,240 --> 00:13:22,240
Of course.

205
00:13:22,610 --> 00:13:24,710
- Hello.
- Hello.

206
00:13:25,110 --> 00:13:26,110
What's all this?

207
00:13:26,710 --> 00:13:28,580
Are you worried I'll embarrass you...

208
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:30,920
in front of your blind date
if I go dressed like this?

209
00:13:31,220 --> 00:13:33,150
Come on. Why would you say that?

210
00:13:33,150 --> 00:13:35,550
How can you be so hard on yourself?
That's not like you.

211
00:13:35,850 --> 00:13:38,190
You're Oh Jang Mi.
You shine wherever you go.

212
00:13:39,290 --> 00:13:41,890
- That was so cheesy.
- Minus ten points.

213
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:43,860
Do that again
and I'm taking off more points.

214
00:13:45,960 --> 00:13:47,360
Hurry and go try it on.

215
00:13:48,100 --> 00:13:49,400
I hope you like it.

216
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:52,970
The clothes?
Do I have to accept these too?

217
00:13:53,370 --> 00:13:55,240
I told you I don't like
owing you anything.

218
00:13:55,240 --> 00:13:57,880
This isn't a debt.
This time, I'm the one in your debt.

219
00:13:58,180 --> 00:14:00,380
You're the one helping me out this time.

220
00:14:47,830 --> 00:14:49,930
What happened to the Jang Mi
I used to know?

221
00:14:51,360 --> 00:14:53,200
What are you talking about?
I'm right here.

222
00:14:55,700 --> 00:14:57,200
Look...

223
00:14:57,870 --> 00:14:58,870
Here.

224
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:03,310
You're just borrowing it,
so don't feel pressured. Go on, try it on.

225
00:15:03,770 --> 00:15:05,840
It'll complete the look.

226
00:15:09,850 --> 00:15:11,020
This looks expensive.

227
00:15:11,850 --> 00:15:13,780
If I wear this and end up losing it,

228
00:15:13,850 --> 00:15:16,790
am I going to have to pay you back
like last time with the guitar?

229
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:18,490
I doubt you'd lose it.

230
00:15:19,290 --> 00:15:20,660
Go ahead, try it on.

231
00:15:21,060 --> 00:15:23,660
This is just for you
to play your part convincingly.

232
00:15:24,130 --> 00:15:26,100
It's all part of the look we're going for.

233
00:15:28,430 --> 00:15:31,140
- Do you want me to put it on for you?
- No, I'll do it.

234
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:33,400
There.

235
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:36,670
This is kind of a heavy load on me.

236
00:15:55,090 --> 00:15:57,730
Stop staring.
You're going to stare a hole through me.

237
00:15:58,900 --> 00:15:59,930
Happy now?

238
00:16:03,500 --> 00:16:04,640
Okay, I get it.

239
00:16:05,670 --> 00:16:07,170
I'd better stop before I stare a hole
right through you.

240
00:16:10,340 --> 00:16:11,340
Oh, my.

241
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:18,950
How about this one?

242
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:21,890
No.

243
00:16:23,590 --> 00:16:24,820
What about this one?

244
00:16:26,360 --> 00:16:27,360
I don't like it.

245
00:16:30,730 --> 00:16:32,330
This is pretty.

246
00:16:35,170 --> 00:16:36,300
Looks pretty good on me, don't you think?

247
00:16:37,130 --> 00:16:39,900
- Come over here.
- Where are we going?

248
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:43,210
- I said, come here.
- Where are you taking me now?

249
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:46,610
- Maybe I should get a necklace, too.
- Ma'am.

250
00:16:52,080 --> 00:16:53,350
Let's get you a necklace, too.

251
00:16:53,750 --> 00:16:56,490
No way.
Do you have any idea how much these cost?

252
00:16:56,550 --> 00:16:57,550
I can't.

253
00:16:57,860 --> 00:16:59,020
Why not?

254
00:16:59,490 --> 00:17:00,720
Just pick one.

255
00:17:03,560 --> 00:17:04,800
Which one looks better on me?

256
00:17:16,510 --> 00:17:19,810
Hong Ju, it's Mom. I'm at the hotel.

257
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:21,880
Isn't Chae Hwa Young going anywhere today?

258
00:17:22,180 --> 00:17:23,710
I'm bored to death over here.

259
00:17:24,450 --> 00:17:25,850
And I'm starving to death.

260
00:17:32,190 --> 00:17:34,860
- You're the first.
- What?

261
00:17:34,990 --> 00:17:38,900
The first man to keep refusing a date
with a Supreme Court justice's daughter.

262
00:17:40,700 --> 00:17:42,770
That's why I even asked my uncle
for a favor...

263
00:17:43,330 --> 00:17:44,870
to add some pressure.

264
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:47,870
I told him I absolutely had to meet you.

265
00:17:49,470 --> 00:17:51,180
He's the president of the bar association,
you see.

266
00:17:55,280 --> 00:17:57,880
It seems my efforts paid off.

267
00:18:01,220 --> 00:18:02,390
Lawyer Kang,

268
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:04,890
you seem like the type
who's all work and no play.

269
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:06,760
Really?

270
00:18:07,060 --> 00:18:10,990
I'm a bigger player than Casanova,
and I practically live at the clubs.

271
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:17,700
- Okay.
- What? You don't believe me?

272
00:18:17,770 --> 00:18:19,400
Your mother said...

273
00:18:19,870 --> 00:18:22,510
that you rejected all the other women
she tried to set you up with.

274
00:18:24,910 --> 00:18:26,510
What do you think now that
you've met me in person?

275
00:18:27,010 --> 00:18:29,750
Be honest. I used to be a model, you know.

276
00:18:39,420 --> 00:18:42,430
Excuse me. This man is mine.

277
00:18:43,490 --> 00:18:44,500
"My man?"

278
00:18:46,200 --> 00:18:47,200
What did you just say?

279
00:18:50,370 --> 00:18:51,600
Is this some kind of joke?

280
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:53,340
Jang Mi.

281
00:18:57,270 --> 00:19:00,840
This is no joke.
I don't play games with people's hearts.

282
00:19:01,480 --> 00:19:05,120
Honey, could you really leave me
and marry another woman?

283
00:19:06,720 --> 00:19:08,250
Could you?

284
00:19:10,090 --> 00:19:12,990
I only asked you to wait a little longer,
but you couldn't even do that.

285
00:19:14,260 --> 00:19:17,490
Do you have any idea
how high-maintenance you are?

286
00:19:24,570 --> 00:19:27,670
I'm so sorry.
I had no idea this would happen.

287
00:19:28,140 --> 00:19:30,370
Please smooth it over with your parents.

288
00:19:30,370 --> 00:19:32,080
Tell them
you aren't interested in me anymore.

289
00:19:36,850 --> 00:19:39,080
You two make a great couple.

290
00:19:39,520 --> 00:19:43,320
I wish you two all the best.

291
00:19:56,100 --> 00:19:57,100
It worked.

292
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:12,620
That was an act, but it was so much fun.

293
00:20:12,820 --> 00:20:14,350
I think I have a knack for acting.

294
00:20:14,450 --> 00:20:15,790
You were actually really good.

295
00:20:16,220 --> 00:20:18,490
And that part earlier,
when you called me your man,

296
00:20:19,590 --> 00:20:21,430
it felt so real
and made my heart skip a beat.

297
00:20:23,130 --> 00:20:24,130
Well...

298
00:20:24,330 --> 00:20:25,460
Come on.

299
00:20:26,130 --> 00:20:27,160
The truth is,

300
00:20:27,970 --> 00:20:29,570
I really want to be your man, Jang Mi.

301
00:20:34,570 --> 00:20:35,570
Here.

302
00:20:36,710 --> 00:20:39,280
If you ever lose this,
I'll always find it for you.

303
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:42,210
Your good luck.

304
00:20:43,850 --> 00:20:48,290
I'm only taking this because I'm afraid
my good luck will pass me by if I don't.

305
00:20:48,650 --> 00:20:49,750
So don't get the wrong idea.

306
00:21:05,700 --> 00:21:06,700
Oh my.

307
00:21:09,240 --> 00:21:10,340
Where on earth am I?

308
00:21:12,510 --> 00:21:13,710
Oh my, what time is it?

309
00:21:14,710 --> 00:21:15,980
Looks like everyone's left for the day.

310
00:21:18,980 --> 00:21:22,850
Darn it. Tailing someone is no joke.

311
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:24,120
What a mess.

312
00:21:26,060 --> 00:21:27,120
I'm aching all over.

313
00:21:27,990 --> 00:21:29,060
My back...

314
00:21:32,960 --> 00:21:34,330
Oh my, that's Chae Hwa Young.

315
00:21:46,410 --> 00:21:48,880
That's him. That's my son.

316
00:21:49,650 --> 00:21:51,150
The date of birth is the same.

317
00:21:51,980 --> 00:21:53,550
"199005."

318
00:21:54,180 --> 00:21:55,390
What's that?

319
00:21:55,750 --> 00:21:57,090
Is that a date of birth?

320
00:22:01,830 --> 00:22:03,030
What are you doing?

321
00:22:04,730 --> 00:22:06,200
1990.

322
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:08,330
May 29th.

323
00:22:09,230 --> 00:22:10,670
It's my Ha Neul's birthday.

324
00:22:14,100 --> 00:22:15,270
What do I do?

325
00:22:18,140 --> 00:22:20,810
I have to find out everything
there is to know about Kang Jun Ho.

326
00:22:22,180 --> 00:22:24,380
It's not like I've done a DNA test yet.

327
00:22:28,190 --> 00:22:29,920
Kang Jun Ho can't be my son.

328
00:22:30,390 --> 00:22:31,490
He must not be my son.

329
00:23:21,870 --> 00:23:22,970
What if Kang Jun Ho...

330
00:23:23,970 --> 00:23:25,880
is my son Ha Neul?

331
00:23:27,510 --> 00:23:29,610
No, that can't be right.

332
00:23:39,420 --> 00:23:41,260
- Honey.
- Yes?

333
00:23:41,630 --> 00:23:43,590
Where are you going at this hour?

334
00:23:45,000 --> 00:23:46,330
Well, you know...

335
00:23:46,930 --> 00:23:49,130
Just to get some fresh air.

336
00:23:49,730 --> 00:23:50,970
Fresh air?

337
00:23:51,500 --> 00:23:53,170
You'll catch a cold.

338
00:23:53,540 --> 00:23:56,370
Don't worry, I'm fine. I'll be right back.

339
00:24:12,490 --> 00:24:14,020
- Hey!
- Dad!

340
00:24:14,190 --> 00:24:15,260
What?

341
00:24:15,260 --> 00:24:17,190
- Jun Ho, are you coming back from work?
- Yes.

342
00:24:17,360 --> 00:24:18,360
Have you eaten?

343
00:24:18,760 --> 00:24:22,270
- I'll just have a beer before bed.
- Okay. Hurry inside. It's cold.

344
00:24:23,130 --> 00:24:26,400
So Kang Jun Ho is Professor Kang's son?

345
00:24:27,670 --> 00:24:30,570
No way. How can this be?

346
00:24:33,140 --> 00:24:34,140
So that's it.

347
00:24:35,050 --> 00:24:38,050
So that's why Professor Kang had a photo
of my Ha Neul in his wallet.

348
00:24:54,560 --> 00:24:55,800
Hello, Professor.

349
00:24:56,670 --> 00:24:59,340
Hwa Young, where are you? Are you busy?

350
00:25:00,300 --> 00:25:01,300
Well...

351
00:25:01,300 --> 00:25:02,340
I miss you.

352
00:25:02,610 --> 00:25:04,710
Can't I see you, even for just a moment?

353
00:25:07,110 --> 00:25:08,110
Actually...

354
00:25:09,150 --> 00:25:11,150
I'm in your neighborhood.

355
00:25:11,150 --> 00:25:12,420
Really?

356
00:25:13,180 --> 00:25:14,280
Where are you?

357
00:25:30,200 --> 00:25:31,870
Oh my, who's that?

358
00:25:34,100 --> 00:25:35,640
I got you.

359
00:26:00,800 --> 00:26:02,500
Where's my camera?

360
00:26:02,500 --> 00:26:06,040
I need to get photo evidence
of this crucial moment.

361
00:26:06,940 --> 00:26:11,470
Look how smart I am.
My gut is never wrong.

362
00:26:12,240 --> 00:26:13,510
Look at that.

363
00:26:13,510 --> 00:26:14,980
She's definitely seeing a man.

364
00:26:15,310 --> 00:26:18,320
Look at them. They're all over each other.

365
00:26:30,360 --> 00:26:32,960
I guess this means it's game over, right?

366
00:26:35,270 --> 00:26:37,130
Chairman, we have a huge problem.

367
00:26:37,500 --> 00:26:39,470
What's all the fuss about?

368
00:26:39,800 --> 00:26:42,970
It's confirmed
that CEO Chae is seeing a man.

369
00:26:43,610 --> 00:26:45,280
Good grief.

370
00:26:49,910 --> 00:26:51,680
Here, look at this.

371
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:56,420
She's having drinks with a man,

372
00:26:56,790 --> 00:26:59,660
and look how smitten they are
with each other.

373
00:26:59,990 --> 00:27:02,290
When you, her father-in-law,
are right under the same roof.

374
00:27:02,730 --> 00:27:04,190
How could she...

375
00:27:04,360 --> 00:27:08,370
It's always the quiet ones, isn't it?

376
00:27:10,030 --> 00:27:11,740
How could she betray you,

377
00:27:12,300 --> 00:27:15,540
no, our entire company, Dream?
There's a line you don't cross, you know.

378
00:27:16,670 --> 00:27:18,480
She can't get away with this, Chairman.

379
00:27:45,970 --> 00:27:47,570
(The First Man)

380
00:27:47,640 --> 00:27:51,980
I need to know for sure if Kang Jun Ho
is really our Ha Neul.

381
00:27:52,410 --> 00:27:54,340
I can't be sure
based on circumstances alone.

382
00:27:54,510 --> 00:27:57,110
I want to be your man, Jang Mi.

383
00:27:57,110 --> 00:27:58,650
And I know you like me too.

384
00:27:58,980 --> 00:28:01,720
Please, be my woman.

385
00:28:02,090 --> 00:28:04,250
The Chairman wants you in his study.

386
00:28:04,620 --> 00:28:05,620
What's this about?

387
00:28:06,020 --> 00:28:08,120
What have you been up to every night?

388
00:28:08,120 --> 00:28:09,490
I'm asking you, what have you been up to?

389
00:28:10,730 --> 00:28:12,730
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
